parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Light Control Module (LCM) can cause the headlights to shut off suddenly, leading to reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: fog lights and running lights continue to function
no warning lights or indicators on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of original equipment manufacturer (OEM) tires can lead to safety hazards, as drivers are forced to use incorrect size tires or continue to drive on worn-out tires, increasing the risk of accidents and fatalities.
symptoms: forced to use incorrect size tires
and uncertainty about the production date of the required tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Damage due to Road Hazards
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hitting a pothole or other road hazards can cause tire damage, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The close proximity of the brake and accelerator pedals can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, property damage, and potential injuries.
symptoms: the brake pedal is too close to the gas pedal
the gas pedal is too sensitive
the driver unknowingly depresses the accelerator pedal while pressing the brake or vice versa

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to continue rolling or surging forward, leading to accidents, property damage, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to roll after braking
the brakes fail to engage properly
the vehicle collides with another vehicle or object.
